{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Within my prison cell so [D7]dreary
[G]Alone I sit with weary heart
[D7]I'm thinking of my lonely darling
[G]From her forever I must part
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[D7]A rose she sent me as a token
[G]She sent it just to light my gloom
[D7]To tell me that her heart was broken
[G]To cheer me fore I meet my doom
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[D7]She wrote I took it from the garden
[G]Where once we wandered side by side
[D7]But now you hold no hope of pardon
[G]And I can never be your bride
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[D7]That old judge would not believe my story
[G]The jury said I have to pay
[D7]Now to the rose and all its glory
[G]Not guilty is all that I can say
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[D7]Goodbye sweetheart for in the morning
[G]I'll meet my Maker and repose
[D7]And when I go at daylight darling
[G]Against my heart they'll find your rose
{end_of_verse}




